DISCLAIMER:

This software is provided for EDUCATIONAL and RESEARCH purposes only. 
ScamShield is designed as a defensive security tool to help users identify 
potential scam communications.

This software does NOT:
- Intercept phone calls or messages without user consent
- Perform any offensive security operations
- Violate any laws or regulations
- Guarantee 100% accuracy in scam detection

Users are responsible for:
- Using this software in compliance with local laws
- Making their own judgments about communication safety
- Reporting suspected scams to appropriate authorities
- Understanding the limitations of automated detection

The authors and contributors are not liable for:
- Missed scam detections (false negatives)
- Incorrectly flagged legitimate communications (false positives)
- Any damages resulting from use of this software
- Actions taken based on the software's recommendations

For actual scam incidents, always contact:
- Federal Trade Commission (FTC): https://reportfraud.ftc.gov
- FBI Internet Crime Complaint Center (IC3): https://www.ic3.gov
- Local law enforcement authorities
